  <refnamediv>
    <refname>corr2</refname>
    <refpurpose>2D correlation coefficient</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Syntax</title>
   <synopsis>
   c = corr2(imA, imB)
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>imA, imB :</term>
      <listitem><para> imA and imB are 2D matrices of the same size.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>c :</term>
      <listitem><para> Correlation coefficient, a scalar of class double.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
corr2 computes correlation coefficient of two 2D matrices imA and imB.
c = sum( (imA-mA).*(imB-mB) / sqrt(sum((imA-mA).^2) * sum((imB-mB).^2))
mA=mean2(imA) and mB=mean2(imB)
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

